    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Veils or shawls worn across the shoulders of altar servers, to cover their hands when carrying the mitre and crosier during liturgical functions and processions. For veils that are similar but larger, and worn by the priest or other celebrant, prefer "humeral veils."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
